# Project Domain Rules (HIGH PRIORITY)

Read this before making changes.

The project is organized into domains.

You MUST:

- Identify which domain work belongs to
- Stay inside the requested domain
- Warn before crossing domains
- Avoid redesigning previous domains unless explicitly requested
- Use Project Source of Truth as higher authority

---

# Domain 1 — Foundation + Architecture [ARCH]

Purpose:

Core architecture and standards.

Owns:

- routing
- layouts
- folder structure
- state patterns
- docs
- testing rules
- naming conventions
- architecture decisions

Does NOT own:

- teacher workflows
- AI logic
- cloud implementation
- design polish

---

# Domain 2 — Teacher Story Creation [STORY]

Purpose:

Fast teacher first drafts — minimal setup, generate quickly, refine after generation.

Owns:

- setup forms (required fields + collapsed Advanced options)
- fast create → generate flow (no pre-generation review on happy path)
- post-generation review / refine (create preview + story detail editing)
- validation (required fields for generate; optional fields deferred)
- story planning inputs
- series selection (when wired)

Principles:

- **Minimum required inputs** upfront — lesson goal, theme, setting, story moments, age, language, page count
- **Optional inputs** in Advanced options (title, vocabulary, characters, notes)
- **Generate from the create form** — same `StorySetupInput` contract as before
- **Refine later** on generated preview or story detail — not before first draft

Does NOT own:

- storage implementation (Domain 3)
- authentication (Domain 4)
- AI pipeline / prompts (Domain 6)

See: [docs/domain-2-teacher-flow.md](../docs/domain-2-teacher-flow.md)

---

# Domain 3 — Workspace + Persistence [WORKSPACE]

Purpose:

Make stories reusable — library, detail, editing, drafts, and simple versioning.

Owns:

- drafts and saved stories (library partition: plans vs finished)
- story dashboard (`/dashboard/stories`)
- story detail pages and dual edit surfaces (Quick edit + Advanced editor)
- draft reopen flows (`?draftId=`, continue editing)
- duplicate, archive, delete workflows
- version counter + snapshot history surfacing
- persistence API (`storyStorageApi`)

Principles:

- **Plans** reopen at create form; **finished stories** open on detail
- **Quick edit** on detail for small changes; **Advanced editor** at `/edit` for structure + history
- **`version`** increments on each edit save; snapshots capped at 10 per story (local)
- **Duplicate** resets version; does not copy history or assignments

Does NOT own:

- cloud infrastructure / Supabase schema (Domain 4)
- AI generation systems (Domain 6)
- create form UX (Domain 2)

See: [docs/domain-3-story-workspace.md](../docs/domain-3-story-workspace.md)

